we want to use livesearch, but don't want the space title above the search, and want to change the text on the button.

To make it backwards compatible, I'd suggest supporting:

{livesearch:spaceKey=ABC|title=}
Would remove the title,

{livesearch:spaceKey=ABC|title=xyz}
Would put xyz as the title

{livesearch:spaceKey=ABC}
Would use the default "Searching SpaceName" as the title.

That way, it won't ruin existing searches but would allow us to override the text with a blank. Also, the search box should not render in a div but instead inline, so that:

Search This Space: {livesearch:spaceKey=ABC|title=}

would put the search dialog and button on the same line as 'search this space:'.

also, the default button text can still be 'go', but using the 'buttontext=Search This Space' you can change the button text.
